Results 
As a first step in the computation of asymptotic modes for charged and
rotating black holes we have checked that our numerical methods
reproduce known results in the Schwarzschild limit. In
particular, we have verified the asymptotic behaviour found by Nollert
. His main result was that the real part of the asymptotic
QNM frequencies corresponding to gravitational  perturbations can
be well fitted by a relation of the form
